Sending GET requests

Send requests with key/value pairing
curl '[URL]?[KEY]=[VALUE]'

Send requests with multiple key/value pairings
curl '[URL]?[KEY]=[VALUE]&[KEY]=[VALUE]'

Send requests with a cookie key/value pairing
curl [URL] -H 'Cookie: [KEY]=[VALUE]' -v

Send requests with Content-Type set
curl [URL] -H 'Content-Type:  [KEY]/[VALUE]' -v

Send requests with Accept-Language set
curl [URL] -H 'Accept-Language: [KEY]-[VALUE]' -v

Send request with multiple header options
curl "[DOMAIN]" -H '[HEADER1]: [VALUE]' -H '[HEADER2]: [VALUE]' -v

Send request without squashing specified path
curl "[DOMAIN]/../[OTHERPARTOFDOMAIN]" --path-as-is -v



Sending POST requests

Send POST request with key/value pairing
curl  [URL] --data '[KEY]=[VALUE]'

Send requests with multiple key/value pairings
curl  [URL] --data '[KEY]=[VALUE]&[KEY]=[VALUE]' -v

Send a POST request with both a GET and POST parameter
curl '[URL]?[KEY]=[VALUE]' --data '[KEY]=[VALUE]' 
